Given an integer array nums, return all the triplets [nums[i], nums[j], nums[k]] such that i != j, i != k, and j != k, and nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k] == 0.

Notice that the solution set must not contain duplicate triplets.





intuition - we are separating positive,negative and zeroes.CHange the array n and p into set N and P. If there are 3 zeroes then we are appending it to result set.
            now check that for every element of P, there is no inverse present,if there is then create a subset of those number with a zero and add them to result.
            now use nested loop in n and check whether the sum of 2 elements is present in p,do it for the p now. Return result





class Solution:
    def threeSum(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]: 
        res = set()
        n,p,z=[],[],[]
        for num in nums:
            if num > 0:
                p.append(num)
            elif num < 0: 
                n.append(num)
            else:
                z.append(num)
        N, P = set(n), set(p)
        if z:
            for num in P:
                if -1*num in N:
                    res.add((-1*num, 0, num))
        if len(z) >= 3:
            res.add((0,0,0))
        for i in range(len(n)):
            for j in range(i+1,len(n)):
                target = -1*(n[i]+n[j])
                if target in P:
                    res.add(tuple(sorted([n[i],n[j],target])))
        for i in range(len(p)):
            for j in range(i+1,len(p)):
                target = -1*(p[i]+p[j])
                if target in N:
                    res.add(tuple(sorted([p[i],p[j],target])))

        return res





2 years later - 
intuition - break the array into +ve,-ve and 0s. Make the +ve and -ve array into sets. If there is a single zero then check if there are ame element with opposite sign exist, if so add those numbers with 0 into
            into the res set. If +ve array is a number that equal to the um of 2 negaative number multiplied by -1, add those 3 number in the res set. CHeck in case of -ve set. Return res in array form
            because output cannot be set form






class Solution:
    def threeSum(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:

        res = set()

        n, p, z = [], [], []
        for num in nums:
            if num > 0:
                p.append(num)
            elif num < 0: 
                n.append(num)
            else:
                z.append(num)

        N, P = set(n), set(p)

        if z:
            for num in P:
                if -1*num in N:
                    res.add((-1*num, 0, num))

        if len(z) >= 3:
            res.add((0,0,0))

        for i in range(len(n)):
            for j in range(i+1,len(n)):
                target = -1*(n[i]+n[j])
                if target in P:
                    res.add(tuple(sorted([n[i],n[j],target])))

        for i in range(len(p)):
            for j in range(i+1,len(p)):
                target = -1*(p[i]+p[j])
                if target in N:
                    res.add(tuple(sorted([p[i],p[j],target])))
                    

        return list(res)
